## JSS MARKING SCHEME (Total: 65 marks)

### PART A — Written Communication (Session 1) — Max: 20 marks
| # | Criterion | Max Score |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Write-up neatly and logically organized (clearly labeled sections, plagiarism pledge) | 2 |
| 2 | Evidence of background research in write-up | 1 |
| 3 | Written language in write-up or display board (legible, correct fonts, no spelling mistakes) | 1 |
| 4 | Objectives reflected in write-up and display board | 2 |
| 5 | Methods and materials used in write-up and display board | 2 |
| 6 | Results in write-up and display board (tabular + graphs) | 2 |
| 7 | Analysis of results in write-up or display board | 1 |
| 8 | Discussion of results (patterns, trends, anomalies, limitations) | 1 |
| 9 | Future possibilities / recommendations | 1 |
| 10 | Conclusions (valid, based on findings, linked to objectives) | 1 |
| 11 | References (correct format) | 1 |
| 12 | Acknowledgements | 1 |
| 13 | Display board (correct size, logical flow, neatly organized) | 2 |
| 14 | Project data file / Portfolio | 2 |
| **TOTAL** | | **20** |

**Scoring levels for JSS Part A:**
- Max 1.0: BE=0.25, AE=0.5, ME=0.75, EE=1.0
- Max 2.0: BE=0.5, AE=1.0, ME=1.5, EE=2.0

### PART B — Oral Communication (Session 2) — Max: 10 marks
| # | Criterion | Max Score |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Enthusiasm / effort | 1 |
| 2 | Voice / tone (audible, varying intonation) | 1 |
| 3 | Self-confidence | 1 |
| 4 | Scientific language | 2 |
| 5 | Response to questions | 2 |
| 6 | Limitations / weaknesses and gaps | 1 |
| 7 | Possible suggestions / recommendations | 1 |
| 8 | Authenticity (ownership of project) | 1 |
| **TOTAL** | | **10** |

### PART C — Scientific Thought, Method and Creativity (Session 2) — Max: 35 marks
| # | Criterion | Max Score |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Statement of the problem and objectives | 2 |
| 2 | Introduction / Background information | 2 |
| 3 | Application of scientific concepts to everyday life | 3 |
| 4 | Subject mastery | 3 |
| 5 | Literature review | 2 |
| 6 | Data adequacy | 3 |
| 7 | Variables defined and controlled | 2 |
| 8 | Statement of originality | 2 |
| 9 | Logical sequence: Apparatus (2) + Procedure (2) + Illustrations (3) | 7 |
| 10 | Linkage to emerging issues | 2 |
| 11 | Originality | 3 |
| 12 | Creativity | 2 |
| 13 | Skill / workmanship | 2 |
| **TOTAL** | | **35** |

**JSS Grand Total: 20 + 10 + 35 = 65 marks**

